'''CROSSFIT INC.'''（{{Lang-en|CrossFit, Inc.}}）是一間美國[[健身|健身]]公司<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=108717962 |title=Bloomberg Businessweek |access-date=2012-12-29 |archive-date=2021-02-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210218025203/https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=478a3330-7194-11eb-8484-6b49a6c0f3df&url=L3Jlc2VhcmNoL3N0b2Nrcy9wcml2YXRlL3NuYXBzaG90LmFzcD9wcml2Y2FwSWQ9MTA4NzE3OTYy |dead-url=no }}</ref>，於 2000 年由 Greg Glassman（及 Lauren Glassman<ref>{{cite web|last=Glassman|first=Greg|title=Nutrition Lecture Part 2: Optimizing Performance|url=http://journal.crossfit.com/2007/11/nutrition-lecture-part-2-optim.tpl|publisher=Crossfit Inc|accessdate=12 August 2012|archive-date=2018-10-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181019190556/http://journal.crossfit.com/2007/11/nutrition-lecture-part-2-optim.tpl|dead-url=yes}}</ref>）創立。公司在全球有 4,400 間（主要位於美國）有聯繫的[[健身室|健身室]]提供CrossFit[[健身計劃|健身計劃]]<ref name="Moser">{{cite news|last=Moser|first=Kate|title=Cross Purposes|url=http://m.montereycountyweekly.com/news/2012/aug/16/cross-purposes/|accessdate=2012-08-24|newspaper=Monterey County Weekly|date=2012-08-16|archive-date=2012-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121029173902/http://m.montereycountyweekly.com/news/2012/aug/16/cross-purposes/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，人們亦會跟隨該公司每天在網站上張貼的新健身動作，以執行 CrossFit 計劃。"CROSSFIT"亦是CROSSFIT, INC.的註冊商標。

Crossfit健身計劃強調身体全面强健，包括[[体能|体能]]、[[力量|力量]]、[[爆发力|爆发力]]、[[速度|速度]]、[[协调性|协调性]]、[[柔韧性|柔韧性]]等等<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.slideshare.net/leeshouse/crossfit-instructor-manual-v4 |title=CrossFit instructor manual |access-date=2011-06-02 |archive-date=2016-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303203413/http://www.slideshare.net/leeshouse/crossfit-instructor-manual-v4 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

Crossfit健身計劃综合了[[田径|田径]]、[[体操|体操]]、[[举重|举重]]等许多动作进行无间歇练习<ref name=canada>{{cite news |first=Jill |last=Barker |title=Crossfit is fast and furious |url=http://www.canada.com/topics/lifestyle/fitness/story.html?id=a5a28fa9-2973-47c3-a4cc-60ce020f309e&k=19281 |publisher=Montreal Gazette |date=2006-02-14 |accessdate=2007-11-21 |archive-date=2016-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525051943/http://www.canada.com/topics/lifestyle/fitness/story.html?id=a5a28fa9-2973-47c3-a4cc-60ce020f309e&k=19281 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="bestlife">{{cite news |url=http://67.192.124.28/cms/publish/health-fitness/Is_Your_Workout_Wasting_Your_Time.shtml |work=Best Life |date=October 23, 2007 |title=A no-nonsense look at the often nonsensical world of fitness clubs |first=Paul |last=Scott |accessdate=2011-06-02 |archive-date=2008-12-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081205125949/http://67.192.124.28/cms/publish/health-fitness/Is_Your_Workout_Wasting_Your_Time.shtml |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。这种练习方式的基本原则就是，几个动作为一组、不间歇或者稍微间歇的以最快的速度在规定时间下完成尽量多的组，或者在规定组数下以尽量少的时间完成。运动生理学家认为，高强度的全身练习對於体能的實用性增强与健身效果的提高要强於單單改善[[肌肉|肌肉]]外观的孤立肌肉练习([[健美|健美]])。

